cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use AI-Native OS, please cite it as below."
title: "AI-Native OS: The open operating system for building an AI-native company"
abstract: >-
  AI-Native OS is a theme-agnostic, open-source operating system for building companies where
  intelligence sits at the core of the product and the org. It pairs a 15-chapter Handbook and a
  Dictionary of AI-native vocabulary with a runnable library of AI skills, multi-step flows,
  recurring loops, and advisor agents - covering the arc from framing a hypothesis to architecting
  the system, agentic building, evaluation and safety, shipping a Minimum Viable Agent, GEO-driven
  growth, and data moats - across Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, and Gemini CLI.
